  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Acute patients in Denmark are often admitted to Emergency Departments by their General
      Practitioner with a presumptive diagnosis.

      The aim of this study is to evaluate the diagnostic value of the pre-admission presumptive
      diagnosis and to assess if the presumptive diagnosis could be replaced by a number of
      symptom-based groups.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
